<chapter xml:id='chap-standards'
 xmlns='http://docbook.org/ns/docbook'
 version='5.0' xml:lang='en'
 xmlns:xsi='http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance'
 xsi:schemaLocation='http://docbook.org/ns/docbook
                     http://docbook.org/xml/5.0/xsd/docbook.xsd'
 xmlns:xlink='http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink'
 xmlns:xinclude='http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude'>
 <title>Supported Standards</title>

 <para>OpenAM implements the following RFCs, Internet-Drafts, and standards.</para>

 <!-- Document [link], brief description -->
 <variablelist>
  <varlistentry xml:id="oauth-2">
   <term><link xlink:href="http://oauth.net/2/">OAuth 2.0</link></term>
   <listitem>
    <indexterm>
     <primary>Supported standards</primary>
     <secondary>OAuth 2.0</secondary>
    </indexterm>
    <para><link xlink:show="new" xlink:href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6749"
    >The OAuth 2.0 Authorization Framework</link>, in which OpenAM can play the
    roles of authorization server and of client.</para>
    <para><link xlink:show="new" xlink:href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6750"
    >The OAuth 2.0 Authorization Framework: Bearer Token Usage</link>, in which
    OpenAM plays the role of authorization server.</para>
    <para><link xlink:show="new" xlink:href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-oauth-assertions"
    >Assertion Framework for OAuth 2.0</link>, which is an Internet-Draft.</para>
    <para><link xlink:show="new" xlink:href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-oauth-saml2-bearer"
    >SAML 2.0 Bearer Assertion Profiles for OAuth 2.0</link>, which is an
    Internet-Draft.</para>
    <para><link xlink:show="new" xlink:href="http://tools.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-oauth-jwt-bearer"
    >JSON Web Token (JWT) Profile for OAuth 2.0 Client Authentication and
    Authorization Grants</link>, which is an Internet-Draft.</para>
   </listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry xml:id="openid-connect-1">
   <term><link xlink:href="http://openid.net/connect/">OpenID Connect 1.0</link></term>
   <listitem>
    <indexterm>
     <primary>Supported standards</primary>
     <secondary>OpenID Connect 1.0</secondary>
    </indexterm>

    <para>
     OpenAM can be configured to play the role of OpenID provider.
     The OpenID Connect specifications depend on OAuth 2.0,
     JSON Web Token, Simple Web Discovery and related specifications.
     The following specifications make up OpenID Connect 1.0.
    </para>

    <itemizedlist>
     <listitem>
      <para>
       <link xlink:show="new"
             xlink:href="http://openid.net/specs/openid-connect-core-1_0.html"
       >OpenID Connect Core 1.0</link> defines core OpenID Connect 1.0 features.
      </para>
     </listitem>

     <listitem>
      <para>
       <link xlink:show="new"
             xlink:href="http://openid.net/specs/openid-connect-discovery-1_0.html"
       >OpenID Connect Discovery 1.0</link> defines how clients can
       dynamically recover information about OpenID providers.
      </para>
     </listitem>

     <listitem>
      <para>
       <link xlink:show="new"
             xlink:href="http://openid.net/specs/openid-connect-registration-1_0.html"
       >OpenID Connect Dynamic Client Registration 1.0</link> defines how
       clients can dynamically register with OpenID providers.
      </para>
     </listitem>

     <listitem>
      <para>
       <link xlink:show="new"
             xlink:href="http://openid.net/specs/openid-connect-session-1_0.html"
       >OpenID Connect Session Management 1.0</link> describes how
       to manage OpenID Connect sessions, including logout.
      </para>
     </listitem>

     <listitem>
      <para>
       <link xlink:show="new"
             xlink:href="http://openid.net/specs/oauth-v2-multiple-response-types-1_0.html"
       >OAuth 2.0 Multiple Response Type Encoding Practices</link> defines
       additional OAuth 2.0 response types used in OpenID Connect.
      </para>
     </listitem>

     <listitem>
      <para>
       <link xlink:show="new"
             xlink:href="http://openid.net/specs/oauth-v2-form-post-response-mode-1_0.html"
       >OAuth 2.0 Form Post Response Mode</link> defines how OpenID providers
       return OAuth 2.0 Authorization Response parameters in auto-submitting forms.
      </para>
     </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>

    <para>
     OpenID Connect 1.0 also provides implementer's guides for client developers.
    </para>

    <itemizedlist>
     <listitem>
      <para>
       <link xlink:show="new"
             xlink:href="http://openid.net/specs/openid-connect-basic-1_0.html"
       >OpenID Connect Basic Client Implementer's Guide 1.0</link>.
      </para>
     </listitem>

     <listitem>
      <para>
       <link xlink:show="new"
             xlink:href="http://openid.net/specs/openid-connect-implicit-1_0.html"
       >OpenID Connect Implicit Client Implementer's Guide 1.0</link>.
      </para>
     </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
   </listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry xml:id="rest">
   <term><link
   xlink:href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Representational_state_transfer"
   >Representational State Transfer (REST)</link></term>
   <listitem>
    <indexterm>
     <primary>Supported standards</primary>
     <secondary>REST</secondary>
    </indexterm>
    <para>Style of software architecture for web-based, distributed
    systems.</para>
   </listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry xml:id="saml">
   <term><link xlink:href="http://saml.xml.org/" xlink:show="new"
   >Security Assertion Markup Language (SAML)</link></term>
   <listitem>
    <indexterm>
     <primary>Supported standards</primary>
     <secondary>SAML</secondary>
    </indexterm>
    <para>
     Standard, XML-based framework for creating
     and exchanging security information between online partners.
     OpenAM supports multiple versions of SAML including 2.0, 1.1, and 1.0.
    </para>

    <para>
     Specifications are available from the <link xlink:show="new"
     xlink:href="https://www.oasis-open.org/standards">OASIS standards page</link>.
    </para>
   </listitem>
  </varlistentry>

  <varlistentry xml:id="liberty-id-ff">
   <term><link
   xlink:href="http://projectliberty.org/resource_center/specifications/liberty_alliance_id_ff_1_2_specifications/?f=resource_center/specifications/liberty_alliance_id_ff_1_2_specifications"
   >Liberty Alliance Project Identity Federation Framework (Liberty
   ID-FF)</link></term>
   <listitem>
    <indexterm>
     <primary>Supported standards</primary>
     <secondary>Liberty ID-FF</secondary>
    </indexterm>
    <para>Federation standard, whose concepts and capabilities contributed to
    SAML 2.0.</para>
   </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
  <varlistentry xml:id="soap">
   <term><link xlink:href="http://www.w3.org/TR/soap/">Simple Object Access
   Protocol</link></term>
   <listitem>
    <indexterm>
     <primary>Supported standards</primary>
     <secondary>SOAP</secondary>
    </indexterm>
    <para>Lightweight protocol intended for exchanging structured information
    in a decentralized, distributed environment.</para>
   </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
  <varlistentry xml:id="wsdl">
   <term><link xlink:href="http://www.w3.org/TR/wsdl">Web Services Description
   Language (WSDL)</link></term>
   <listitem>
    <indexterm>
     <primary>Supported standards</primary>
     <secondary>WSDL</secondary>
    </indexterm>
    <para>XML format for describing network services as a set of endpoints
    operating on messages containing either document-oriented or
    procedure-oriented information.</para>
   </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
  <varlistentry xml:id="ws-federation">
   <term><link xlink:show="new"
   xlink:href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WS-Federation"
   >Web Services Federation Language (WS-Federation)</link></term>
   <listitem>
    <indexterm>
     <primary>Supported standards</primary>
     <secondary>WS-Federation</secondary>
    </indexterm>
    <para>Identity federation standard, part of the Web Services Security
    framework.</para>
   </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
  <varlistentry xml:id="xacml">
   <term><link xlink:href="http://wiki.oasis-open.org/xacml/">eXtensible Access
   Control Markup Language (XACML)</link></term>
   <listitem>
    <indexterm>
     <primary>Supported standards</primary>
     <secondary>XACML</secondary>
    </indexterm>
    <para>Declarative access control policy language implemented in XML, and
    also a processing model, describing how to interpret policies.</para>
   </listitem>
  </varlistentry>
 </variablelist>
</chapter>
